             was indicted, for <rs id="t18180909-81-off445" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18180909-81-off445" type="offenceCategory" value="deception"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180909-81-off445" type="offenceSubcategory" value="forgery"></interp>
               that he, on the <rs id="t18180909-81-cd446" type="crimeDate">7th of August</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180909-81-off445 t18180909-81-cd446"></join>, at Allhallows, Lombard-street, feloniously did falsely make, forge, and counterfeit, and cause and procure to be falsely made, forged, and coun<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="181809090035"></xptr>terfeited, and willingly act and assist in the false making, forging, and counterfeiting a certain promissory note for payment of money
            </rs>, the tenor of which is as follows:-</p>
               <p>"Bury and Suffolk Bank, No. 864.</p>
               <p>"I promise to pay the bearer Five Pounds, on demand, here or at Messrs. Lees, Satterthwaite, and Brassey, Bankers, London. Bury, 10th November, 1817. For 
